change the parameters so that x is a number

It seems that you'd like to change the parameter `x` to a single number rather than an array representing the spatial domain. In this case, you won't have spatial dependence in the model. I've modified the code below to reflect this change.

``` matlab
% Parameters
D = 1;   % Diffusion coefficient for population
C = 1;   % Diffusion coefficient for information density
r = 0.1;     % Intrinsic growth rate
K = 10^(10*6);   % Carrying capacity
a = -0.01;  % information density effect constant

% Initial conditions
y0 = K/2; % Initial population density
x0 = 0;   % Initial information density

% Discretization in time
T = 50;      % Total simulation time
dt = 0.01;   % Time step
Nt = T/dt;   % Number of time steps
y = y0;
x = x0;

% Time integration using Euler's method
for t = 1:Nt
    % Reaction terms
    fy = r*y*(1 - y/K);
    fx = a*x;

    % Update the solution
    y = y + dt*(fy);
    x = x + dt*(fx);
end

figure(1)
subplot(2, 1, 1);
plot(1:Nt, y); xlabel('Time Step'); ylabel('y'); title('Population Density');
subplot(2, 1, 2);
plot(1:Nt, x); xlabel('Time Step'); ylabel('x'); title('Information Density');

% Time-independent solution
y_steady = K;
x_steady = 0;

figure(2)
subplot(2, 1, 1);
hold on; plot(1:Nt, y_steady * ones(1, Nt)); xlabel('Time Step'); ylabel('y');
subplot(2, 1, 2);
hold on; plot(1:Nt, x_steady * ones(1, Nt)); xlabel('Time Step'); ylabel('x');
```

